Create BuildParentChain(WorkItemViewModel current) method with SIMPLE depth limit for defensive programming. Backend already prevents circular references (work_item.rs:check_circular_reference), so frontend only needs depth limit to handle race conditions or corrupted data gracefully. Use ILogger for warnings, not Console.WriteLine.

CODE SNIPPET:
```csharp
// Add ILogger injection at top of component (around line 12)
@inject ILogger&amp;lt;WorkItemDetail&amp;gt; Logger

// Add method after LoadWorkItemAsync (after line 283)
private List&amp;lt;WorkItemViewModel&amp;gt; BuildParentChain(WorkItemViewModel current)
{
    var chain = new List&amp;lt;WorkItemViewModel&amp;gt;();
    var currentParentId = current.ParentId;
    const int MAX_DEPTH = 20; // Defensive limit (backend has 100)

    // Walk up the parent hierarchy
    while (currentParentId.HasValue &amp;&amp; chain.Count &amp;lt; MAX_DEPTH)
    {
        var parent = AppState.WorkItems.GetById(currentParentId.Value);

        // Edge case: missing parent in cache (orphaned item)
        if (parent is null)
        {
            Logger.LogWarning(
                &quot;Parent {ParentId} not found in cache for work item {WorkItemId}&quot;,
                currentParentId, current.Id);
            break;
        }

        var parentViewModel = ViewModelFactory.Create(parent);
        chain.Add(parentViewModel);
        currentParentId = parent.ParentId;
    }

    // Defensive: log if max depth reached (shouldn&#x27;t happen with backend validation)
    if (chain.Count &amp;gt;= MAX_DEPTH)
    {
        Logger.LogWarning(
            &quot;Max parent chain depth {MaxDepth} reached for work item {WorkItemId}. &quot; +
            &quot;This may indicate data corruption.&quot;,
            MAX_DEPTH, current.Id);
    }

    // Reverse to get top-down order (Epic -&amp;gt; Story -&amp;gt; Task)
    chain.Reverse();
    return chain;
}
```

WHY NO CYCLE DETECTION:
- Backend validates parent changes: `backend/crates/pm-ws/src/handlers/work_item.rs:586-634`
- `check_circular_reference` walks parent chain and rejects cycles
- AppState data is validated by backend, cycles impossible in normal operation
- Frontend depth limit handles edge cases (race conditions, corrupted state)

